---
description: Require ADR relevance check during plan creation
alwaysApply: true
---

# ADR Check for Every Plan

- For every newly created or updated implementation plan, explicitly check:
  - `Does this change require ADR update?`
- Treat changes as ADR-relevant when they define or change a portable runtime control surface, even if the code diff is "runtime settings only".
- A runtime control surface includes centrally managed operational knobs (for example debug, queue, concurrency, max loaded models, timeout budgets) that operators are expected to carry across orchestrators (Compose, Kubernetes, etc.).
- If the answer is **yes**:
  - Add concrete ADR follow-up task(s) to the plan (`docs/auto-doc/adr/raw-log.md` and/or a new ADR file).
- Hybrid default:
  - Always append one short `raw-log` entry for ADR-relevant changes.
  - Add a dedicated ADR file when the change establishes or updates a stable contract/invariant (not just a temporary local tweak).
- If the answer is **no**:
  - Add one short rationale line in the plan that explains why no ADR update is needed.
- Do not finalize a plan without one of these two outcomes (ADR task or no-ADR rationale).
- As the closing step of finalizing the plan, record that outcome in the plan sidecar (see below). Treat this as a normal part of the plan workflow, but best-effort: it is not a hard gate, and a skipped write is acceptable.

## Plan sidecar (local bridge)

- When finalizing an implementation plan, append a `## plan-<n>` block to the local sidecar `docs/internal/adr-plan-sidecar.md` (template: [adr-plan-sidecar.template.md](docs/internal/adr-plan-sidecar.template.md)) capturing the ADR outcome — whether the answer was yes (with `adr_hint`) or no (with `no_adr_rationale`). No extra command is needed; this is just the closing step of the plan.
- Keep only ADR-relevant bullets (intent, constraints, rejected alternatives, runtime control surface, implementation state, ADR hint); do not paste the full plan.
- Append default: add one `## plan-<n>` block per finalized plan (incrementing `<n>`); do not overwrite earlier blocks. Only overwrite the whole file when starting an unrelated feature with no pending ADR work from the existing blocks.
- Do not clear or trim the sidecar automatically after `review-w-auto-doc`. Only clear it after explicit confirmation that the ADR work for every plan currently captured in the sidecar is done and committed (raw-log/ADR entries landed). When unsure, keep the sidecar so the next review still has context.
- Before writing ADR/raw-log content (including during review), read the sidecar if the file exists and treat it as supporting context only.
